<qandaentry><question><para>
What does The Kompany have to do with &KOffice;? Is &KOffice; becoming proprietary?
</para></question><answer><para>
<ulink url="http://www.thekompany.com">The Kompany</ulink> is a company that develops
linux software.  They actively contribute to &KOffice; e.g. by making their applications
Kivio and &Kugar; parts of the &KOffice; suite.  All the programs that have been or will be
incorporated into the official &KOffice; suite are under free licenses (such as GPL or
Artistic) and the incorporated software by The Kompany is no exception.  The &KOffice;
team is very grateful for the contributions The Kompany is putting into &KOffice;.
</para></answer></qandaentry>

